    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-07T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-07T01:00:00-05:00" n="9"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d9">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.24/349²⁄₁₂: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-07T09:00:00+03:00"
                            >May 7, 1942—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 7—8:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>727. My 717, May 6, 9 p.m. [<hi rend="italic">a.m</hi>.] The Middle East Supply
                    Center received a telegram from London indicating that [a representative] from
                    the Maxwell Mission and a civilian sent from Washington are to be American
                    representatives in the Center. The message adds that until the latter arrives an
                    officer will be [designated] from this Legation to serve in his stead. This
                    appears to dispose of the questions raised in my telegram referred to.</p>
                <pb facs="0028" n="16" xml:id="pg_16"/>
                <p>Invitations to attend the Council meetings next week either in person or by
                    alternate are about to be issued to General Maxwell and Jacobs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
